Package coreservlets.lists

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AdvancedOperations
    A few examples of more advanced methods that List supports.
    Autoboxing  
    BasicOperations
    A few examples of the most basic methods that List supports.
    ProcessList1
    The more traditional way to iterate over list elements: by using the same style of for/each loop that we used earlier for arrays.
    ProcessList2
    A newer way to iterate over list elements: by passing each element to a function.
    RandomList
    The first of three examples of the use of Lists.
    RandomListOld
    The second of three examples of the use of Lists, this one using the syntax of Java 5 and 6, which is almost the same as in Java 7 and later except that you must say ArrayList instead of ArrayList<>.
    RandomListVeryOld
    The third of three examples of the use of Lists.
    SimpleList
